TY  - JOUR
T1  - Generational Technological Change: Effects of Innovation and Local Rivalry on Performance
AU  - Lawless, Michael W.
AU  - Anderson, Philip C.
Y1  - 1996/10/01
PY  - 1996
DA  - 1996/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256996
DO  - 10.5465/256996
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 1185
EP  - 1217
VL  - 39
IS  - 5
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We tested the effects of innovation and market complexity on firm performance. Generational technological change?a major advance within a technology regime?fosters the emergence of niches and local rivalry. Findings from the U.S. microcomputer industry between 1982 and 1991 suggest accelerated markets reward innovativeness that differentiates firms within a niche but not across niches. Changing niches confers a short-term penalty. Strong performers adopt new technology quickly, without changing niches.
AB  - We tested the effects of innovation and market complexity on firm performance. Generational technological change?a major advance within a technology regime?fosters the emergence of niches and local rivalry. Findings from the U.S. microcomputer industry between 1982 and 1991 suggest accelerated markets reward innovativeness that differentiates firms within a niche but not across niches. Changing niches confers a short-term penalty. Strong performers adopt new technology quickly, without changing niches.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/256996
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/256996
Y2  - 2026/04/24
