TY  - JOUR
T1  - Is Slack Good or Bad for Innovation?
AU  - Nohria, Nitin
AU  - Gulati, Ranjay
Y1  - 1996/10/01
PY  - 1996
DA  - 1996/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256998
DO  - 10.5465/256998
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 1245
EP  - 1264
VL  - 39
IS  - 5
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This article suggests that there is an inverse U-shaped relationship between slack and innovation in organizations: both too much and too little slack may be detrimental to innovation. Two related mechanisms governing this relationship are proposed: Slack fosters greater experimentation but also diminishing discipline over innovative projects, resulting in the hypothesized curvilinear relationship. Comprehensive worldwide data on 264 functional departments of two multinational corporations support the prediction.
AB  - This article suggests that there is an inverse U-shaped relationship between slack and innovation in organizations: both too much and too little slack may be detrimental to innovation. Two related mechanisms governing this relationship are proposed: Slack fosters greater experimentation but also diminishing discipline over innovative projects, resulting in the hypothesized curvilinear relationship. Comprehensive worldwide data on 264 functional departments of two multinational corporations support the prediction.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/256998
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/256998
Y2  - 2026/04/24
